<HL>
   Harsco Gets Korean Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   HSC FREST
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   HARRISBURG, Pa. -- Harsco Corp. said it received a $260
million four-year contract to supply howitzers to the
Republic of Korea.
   Harsco said it will supply 470 howitzer kits beginning
next year. Samsung Shipbuilding &amp; Heavy Industries will
assemble the howitzers in Korea.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Harsco, a maker of products for defense, industrial,
commercial and construction uses, has been co-producing the
howitzers with Korea since 1984.
</TEXT>
